        "title": "From Apollo to Artemis, the lunar legacy of the Parkes 'Dish' continues",
        "content": {
          "descriptor": {
            "type": "tagname",
            "key": "div",
            "props": {},
            "children": [
              {
                "type": "tagname",
                "key": "@@standfirst",
                "props": {},
                "children": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "content": "The Parkes Observatory — also known as The Dish — continues a legacy of supporting lunar missions that started more than 50 years ago, helping Artemis II go where humanity has not since 1972."
